cs.MA, cs.IR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.ET

Reasoning: 

- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is a likely category as the paper discusses the design of a sensor node that can support numerous smart building applications, which may involve multiple agents working together.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper mentions a predictive algorithm that adapts to changing lighting conditions to maximize node lifetime and application quality of service, which may involve retrieving and processing information.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) and Zig-Bee for wireless communication in smart building applications.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design of a battery-free sensor node using commercial off the shelf components and an ambient light energy harvesting system, which may involve control systems.
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design of a sensor node using commercial off the shelf components and an ambient light energy harvesting system, which may involve embedded systems.
